Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:14.086 --> 01:17.751
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:17.752 --> 01:22.543
♪♪♪

01:22.544 --> 01:27.377
♪♪♪

01:27.378 --> 01:29.044
[metal clanking, crank clicking]

01:32.502 --> 01:34.168
[groans]

01:34.169 --> 01:36.001
I'm not ready...

01:36.368 --> 01:38.314
Worm is always ready
for the hook.

01:38.316 --> 01:40.231
No.
Not ready.

01:40.232 --> 01:41.773
Let me down.

01:42.982 --> 01:44.064
[exhales heavily]

01:44.065 --> 01:45.689
[crank clicking]

01:45.690 --> 01:48.273
[groans]
No. Seriously.

01:48.274 --> 01:49.315
[clicking continues]

01:49.316 --> 01:50.316
Red.

01:50.317 --> 01:52.315
[clicking stops]

01:52.316 --> 01:55.148
Ah.
The safe word.

01:55.149 --> 01:58.898
So you don't think you've earned
your punishment yet?

01:58.899 --> 02:02.148
Fine.

02:02.149 --> 02:04.731
Don't come back
until you have.

02:04.732 --> 02:06.440
♪ Pete Townshend's
"Behind Blue Eyes" ♪

02:06.441 --> 02:08.646
[sighs]

02:08.648 --> 02:12.023
♪ No one knows what it's like ♪

02:12.024 --> 02:15.814
♪ To be the bad man ♪
[glass thuds]

02:15.815 --> 02:19.647
♪ To be the sad man ♪

02:19.648 --> 02:23.398
♪ Behind blue eyes ♪

02:23.399 --> 02:26.731
♪ No one knows what it's like ♪

02:26.732 --> 02:30.522
♪ To be hated ♪

02:30.523 --> 02:33.315
♪ To be fated ♪

02:33.316 --> 02:34.731
When you look at it,

02:34.732 --> 02:36.856
do you see the innocence
everyone talks about?

02:36.857 --> 02:40.440
I guess. But I start thinking
about the man who painted it.

02:40.441 --> 02:41.856
Not so innocent.

02:41.857 --> 02:44.440
'Cause he was a stockbroker
first? Unfair.

02:44.441 --> 02:45.689
Oh, you relate
to him?

02:45.690 --> 02:48.148
Well. Let me see:

02:48.149 --> 02:50.898
he was always broke,
hounded by his creditors,

02:50.899 --> 02:53.231
had a wicked case of syphilis
and liked to marry teenagers.

02:53.232 --> 02:56.731
So, you know,
not really.

02:56.732 --> 02:58.106
He could have
lived like a king

02:58.107 --> 02:59.898
for a lifetime
on what you paid for this.

02:59.899 --> 03:02.106
Not how it works, sadly.

03:02.107 --> 03:05.106
The great ones--
they all have to suffer

03:05.107 --> 03:06.772
to make something like this.

03:06.773 --> 03:08.731
And then usually they only
get the recognition

03:08.732 --> 03:10.273
once they're in the dirt.

03:10.274 --> 03:12.647
There's no rule that says
the greater you want to be,

03:12.648 --> 03:13.814
the more you have
to suffer.

03:13.815 --> 03:16.481
Well.
Sure seems like there is.

03:16.482 --> 03:18.398
I mean,
look at Wendy...

03:18.399 --> 03:20.106
Mm.

03:20.107 --> 03:22.315
I need a favor.

03:22.316 --> 03:25.689
You know, this whole
medical license thing--

03:25.690 --> 03:27.898
she could do with a distraction,
a reset.

03:27.899 --> 03:29.522
What are you thinking?

03:29.523 --> 03:31.564
A state changer.

03:31.565 --> 03:33.814
In the Hamptons,
a spa?

03:33.815 --> 03:35.772
I have my chopper
standing by at the ready.

03:35.773 --> 03:38.231
No fucking spa.
Um...

03:38.232 --> 03:40.148
I have an idea.

03:40.149 --> 03:42.440
Oh. Good.

03:42.441 --> 03:44.273
Why not you?

03:44.274 --> 03:47.356
I have the feeling she'll get
a lot more out of your insights.

03:47.357 --> 03:50.231
Sure.

03:50.232 --> 03:52.481
♪ Pete Townshend's
"Behind Blue Eyes" ♪

03:52.482 --> 03:54.981
♪ No one knows what it's like ♪

03:54.982 --> 03:58.939
♪ To feel these feelings ♪

03:58.940 --> 04:01.522
♪ Like I do ♪

04:01.523 --> 04:05.273
♪ And I blame you ♪

04:05.274 --> 04:09.231
♪ No one bites back as hard ♪

04:09.232 --> 04:10.356
Off to...?

04:10.357 --> 04:11.522
♪ On their anger ♪

04:11.523 --> 04:13.939
Uh. Day trip.
With Rebecca.

04:13.940 --> 04:16.148
State changer.
Or something.

04:16.149 --> 04:17.772
Good.

04:17.773 --> 04:20.106
Yeah.
You let those shoulders drop.

04:20.107 --> 04:22.356
I don't think
they'll drop 'til

04:22.357 --> 04:24.522
the exact terms of my suspension
have been announced.

04:24.523 --> 04:28.440
And probably not
'til it's all over.

04:28.441 --> 04:30.647
While you're gone,
I will be hard at it

04:30.648 --> 04:33.148
trying to get those terms
relaxed or done away.

04:33.149 --> 04:34.856
Would have been easier
ahead of time.

04:34.857 --> 04:37.398
But, uh, there must be
a lever out there.

04:37.399 --> 04:39.564
Too much of that
is what got me here.

04:39.565 --> 04:41.689
Sure.
But you know that now.

04:41.690 --> 04:45.064
Wouldn't you rather repent
with your medical license?

04:45.065 --> 04:48.481
I suppose I would.

04:48.482 --> 04:49.981
Then we've got to
get it done now,

04:49.982 --> 04:51.273
before they
officially rule.

04:51.274 --> 04:52.481
They all but have.

04:52.482 --> 04:54.564
And in that tiny space

04:54.565 --> 04:57.023
between "all" and "have"

04:57.024 --> 04:59.481
lies our hope.

04:59.482 --> 05:02.315
♪ dramatic music ♪

05:02.316 --> 05:06.522
♪♪♪

05:06.523 --> 05:07.689
What's on the docket?

05:07.690 --> 05:09.481
Karl,
I need you to find out

05:09.482 --> 05:11.481
what makes a certain man
light up.

05:11.482 --> 05:12.856
What might move him.

05:12.857 --> 05:14.939
Now, this is a medical man,
name of Zhang, a--

05:14.940 --> 05:16.190
[Jock] Rhoades...
[door opens]

05:16.191 --> 05:18.731
we have business.

05:18.732 --> 05:22.522
What business could we possibly
have, Generalissimo?

05:22.523 --> 05:24.064
The business of men...
[door closes]

05:24.065 --> 05:26.689
one nearly vanquished,
the other ascendent again.

05:26.690 --> 05:28.856
I was taught never to
negotiate with kidnappers.

05:28.857 --> 05:31.106
So, first return my old man,
then, maybe we can--

05:31.107 --> 05:33.522
Move your shit train,
and maybe your old man

05:33.523 --> 05:35.481
will be back in this shit-town
the same day.

05:35.482 --> 05:38.190
Done.
And now our colloquy is over.

05:38.191 --> 05:42.023
Eh. Palaver with me
or just listen.

05:42.024 --> 05:44.231
I give not
a Tinker's-dam.

05:44.232 --> 05:48.064
[sighs]

05:48.065 --> 05:50.606
I am here to offer you
the chance to resign

05:50.607 --> 05:53.106
before I crush you,
publicly,

05:53.107 --> 05:56.231
and loud as a cow elk trying to
squeeze out breached twins.

05:56.232 --> 05:58.731
Oh. You have neither the power
nor the authority.

05:58.732 --> 06:00.522
You once offered me
the chance to surrender

06:00.523 --> 06:02.440
before being visited
by the plagues.

06:02.441 --> 06:05.606
I did not,
and so I paid the price.

06:05.607 --> 06:08.898
Now, I have no desire to bring
dishonor on our profession--

06:08.899 --> 06:11.481
Spare me
your rodomontade.

06:11.482 --> 06:15.481
This is the same bargain you put
to me: the chance to walk away.

06:15.482 --> 06:17.898
With just the bedrock
certainty you had

06:17.899 --> 06:19.398
when you stood
in my kitchen.

06:19.399 --> 06:21.898
You knew that train
was already en route.

06:21.899 --> 06:24.231
I know much the same.

06:24.232 --> 06:26.356
You're done.

06:26.357 --> 06:29.772
You know, you once remarked you
knew all the fancy words I did.

06:29.773 --> 06:32.898
That you'd gone to
the same schools.

06:32.899 --> 06:36.440
Yet you love to deploy
the earthy, the homespun,

06:36.441 --> 06:39.398
the language of the dirt road
and the barefoot walk to school.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.440
[chuckles]

06:41.441 --> 06:45.106
The language, in short,
of your parents and cousins.

06:45.107 --> 06:49.106
Well, I, too, can reach back
into familial lexicon

06:49.107 --> 06:51.522
for bracing truths.

06:51.523 --> 06:55.064
And my, uh--My mother's father
was from Italy...

06:55.065 --> 06:57.273
[chuckles]
...yes, a Roman, you know.

06:57.274 --> 06:59.939
And he taught me that
when someone talks to you

06:59.940 --> 07:01.440
as though you are
of no consequence,

07:01.441 --> 07:02.939
you have two choices.

07:02.940 --> 07:06.064
The first
is to wilt away.

07:06.065 --> 07:10.315
And the second is get right
in their face and tell them...

07:10.316 --> 07:14.148
Sei fuori come un balcone,
figlio di buona donna,

07:14.149 --> 07:17.481
ti venisse un colpo,
a te e a tutta la palazzina tua

07:17.482 --> 07:21.522
ma guardati che sei, burino,
cazzabubbolo, baciapile,

07:21.523 --> 07:23.689
non ti vogliono manco li cani,

07:23.690 --> 07:27.647
sei cosi stronzo che se
pesti una merda fai scopa,

07:27.648 --> 07:31.440
li mortacci tua.

07:31.441 --> 07:33.773
Vaffanculo!
Eh!

07:36.149 --> 07:38.148
[laughs]

07:38.149 --> 07:40.148
[hand pounds]

07:40.149 --> 07:41.939
Oh! That's good.

07:41.940 --> 07:43.772
That is real good, Chuck.
Mm.

07:43.773 --> 07:46.814
[laughing]
That was a good trick.

07:46.815 --> 07:48.356
Ah, a good trick.

07:48.357 --> 07:49.981
I don't understand
a word you said.

07:49.982 --> 07:52.023
Mnm.
But I got the general feeling.

07:52.024 --> 07:53.606
And I like it.

07:53.607 --> 07:55.190
You know why?
Hmm?

07:55.191 --> 07:58.814
Because it tells me that
you are not gonna pay heed.

07:58.815 --> 08:00.356
So let me give you
a final taste

08:00.357 --> 08:02.772
of biscuits
and white gravy American.

08:02.773 --> 08:04.689
You know what happens
to a lumberjack

08:04.690 --> 08:07.689
who doesn't react when
he hears "timber"?

08:07.690 --> 08:10.023
He gets crushed
by a tree.

08:10.024 --> 08:14.939
This case against you
will be complete,

08:14.940 --> 08:17.440
and it is gonna
land on you

08:17.441 --> 08:21.023
like a clear-cut
Ponderosa pine.

08:21.024 --> 08:22.190
[door slams]

08:22.191 --> 08:25.231
♪ dramatic music ♪

08:25.232 --> 08:27.231
♪♪♪

08:27.232 --> 08:29.856
I'm getting back late,

08:29.857 --> 08:34.606
so I will see you at
the board meeting tomorrow.

08:34.607 --> 08:36.522
Yeah. You bet.

08:36.523 --> 08:39.191
Have a great day.

08:40.690 --> 08:41.731
And thank you.

08:41.732 --> 08:42.857
[chuckles]

08:43.899 --> 08:46.898
♪ dramatic music ♪

08:46.899 --> 08:48.731
[button clicks]

08:48.732 --> 08:53.064
♪♪♪

08:53.065 --> 08:57.231
♪♪♪

08:57.232 --> 09:01.440
♪♪♪

09:01.441 --> 09:04.481
[cellphone vibrates]

09:04.482 --> 09:05.814
Hello?

09:05.815 --> 09:08.564
Sandy.
Lemme ask you a question:

09:08.565 --> 09:10.398
You a man who likes
a good breakfast?

09:10.399 --> 09:12.273
Hell yes, I like
a good breakfast.

09:12.274 --> 09:14.148
Then you're gonna love
what I got for ya.

09:14.149 --> 09:15.606
♪♪♪

09:15.607 --> 09:18.273
I hate the expression
"mistakes were made."

09:18.274 --> 09:19.856
Because it avoids blame.

09:19.857 --> 09:21.731
And you know, in all the time
I worked for him,

09:21.732 --> 09:24.106
there were two things I never
heard Bobby Axelrod say:

09:24.107 --> 09:26.273
"I was wrong."
And "I'm sorry."

09:26.274 --> 09:28.064
I'm here to tell you that
that is the last time

09:28.065 --> 09:30.273
you will hear his name come out
of my mouth in this office.

09:30.274 --> 09:32.647
Because I was wrong.
And I am sorry.

09:32.648 --> 09:34.398
I got baited.

09:34.399 --> 09:36.273
Hooked in the mouth
like a trophy marlin.

09:36.274 --> 09:38.106
And narrowly escaped
being mounted on the wall.

09:38.107 --> 09:39.772
But escape I did.
We did.

09:39.773 --> 09:41.606
And now that's the end of it.

09:41.607 --> 09:44.772
We are going to use this moment
to officially, formally,

09:44.773 --> 09:47.190
and in all other ways,
move beyond rivalries,

09:47.191 --> 09:49.190
anger, everything
that doesn't clearly

09:49.191 --> 09:51.440
and demonstrably
help Mase Cap win.

09:51.441 --> 09:53.315
Q is for quantitative,
baby!

09:53.316 --> 09:55.190
[laughter]
That it is.

09:55.191 --> 09:57.689
We will return to
our mathematical model.

09:57.690 --> 09:59.898
And you are now free,
all of you, to maximize,

09:59.899 --> 10:02.106
without fear that I will be
too distracted to notice,

10:02.107 --> 10:05.023
or that I will squander
the resources you are providing.

10:05.024 --> 10:07.440
You are the smartest
and best people in the industry.

10:07.441 --> 10:09.689
And I am proud to
retake my seat amongst you.

10:09.690 --> 10:11.315
Damaged, but reborn.

10:11.316 --> 10:13.856
Taylor Mason is back!
Yeah!

10:13.857 --> 10:15.564
[applause]
[Taylor] More importantly:

10:15.565 --> 10:18.814
Taylor Mason Capital
is back!

10:18.815 --> 10:21.522
[cheers and applause]

10:21.523 --> 10:25.522
♪ mid-tempo music ♪

10:25.523 --> 10:26.981
♪♪♪

10:26.982 --> 10:29.981
[door handle clicks]

10:29.982 --> 10:31.731
[sighs]

10:31.732 --> 10:33.647
Dad.

10:33.648 --> 10:36.148
How are my--

10:36.149 --> 10:38.356
Your consort and child
are fine.

10:38.357 --> 10:39.814
Don't do that.

10:39.815 --> 10:42.106
Her name is Roxanne.

10:42.107 --> 10:44.856
And we call the little girl
Willow.

10:44.857 --> 10:46.856
They're fine, anyway.
How are you?

10:46.857 --> 10:48.315
[horns honking]

10:48.316 --> 10:50.273
I am spent,
to be honest.

10:50.274 --> 10:53.148
When I was young I could've
withstood a bracing like that

10:53.149 --> 10:55.939
while standing on
my fucking head.

10:55.940 --> 10:58.814
But I felt myself fading.

10:58.815 --> 11:01.231
You made it through.

11:01.232 --> 11:02.939
Yeah.

11:02.940 --> 11:06.856
But, Sonny, they are
coming for you strong.

11:06.857 --> 11:08.647
I hope you're ready.

11:08.648 --> 11:10.606
I hope so, too.

11:10.607 --> 11:12.356
♪ dramatic music ♪

11:12.357 --> 11:14.398
You are my boss. So you get
to have me stand here.

11:14.399 --> 11:17.315
But you don't get to ask me
the same question 17 times.

11:17.316 --> 11:19.231
Or rather, you do,
but I don't have to answer it.

11:19.232 --> 11:20.606
Let me ask it
differently then,

11:20.607 --> 11:22.106
since I'm not doing it
to fuck around

11:22.107 --> 11:24.106
but rather to make a case,
which is,

11:24.107 --> 11:26.231
lest we think we are here
to do the double dutch,

11:26.232 --> 11:27.731
the entire reason
for our existence.

11:27.732 --> 11:29.231
Mm.
Feels like double dutch.

11:29.232 --> 11:30.939
Jumping in place.
Tripping over ourselves.

11:30.940 --> 11:32.315
No way you trip doing--

11:32.316 --> 11:34.772
Nope. I can go for hours.
But I bet you would.

11:34.773 --> 11:36.898
Kate, this has gotten off track.
I just need to know,

11:36.899 --> 11:39.440
and not officially--
but for myself, to plan--

11:39.441 --> 11:40.898
if anyone is mentioned

11:40.899 --> 11:42.731
in the privileged part
of that recording.

11:42.732 --> 11:44.106
Anyone material
to the case.

11:44.107 --> 11:46.898
Eighteen. And I can't answer,
won't answer.

11:46.899 --> 11:48.606
How do we know the agents
stopped listening

11:48.607 --> 11:49.981
at just the right moment.

11:49.982 --> 11:50.982
Maybe, after--
No, no.

11:50.983 --> 11:53.023
They, and I,
heard it all.

11:53.024 --> 11:54.856
Best for everyone
you don't listen.

11:54.857 --> 11:56.231
Then I won't get Chuck.

11:56.232 --> 11:58.606
Can you live with that--
Oh. Say you do get him.

11:58.607 --> 12:00.814
Do you think you can ratchet
back the Jack Torrance shit?

12:00.815 --> 12:02.273
Like from The Shining?

12:02.274 --> 12:04.231
Yeah. You have that same
obsessed look in your eye.

12:04.232 --> 12:06.772
The difference is: I'm not
seeing ghosts riding Big Wheels.

12:06.773 --> 12:08.231
I'm seeing a wrongdoer
getting away.

12:08.232 --> 12:10.231
Once he's nailed--
and Jock is pacified--

12:10.232 --> 12:12.481
I'll be free of
all this... stuff.

12:12.482 --> 12:14.647
And the Southern District
will become sovereign again.

12:14.648 --> 12:17.273
In the cause of all that is
good and nob--

12:17.274 --> 12:18.689
and don't you want to
be a part of that?

12:18.690 --> 12:20.106
I do.

12:20.107 --> 12:22.023
Then just tell me this:

12:22.024 --> 12:25.023
does the recording spell out
who the idiot is?

12:25.024 --> 12:26.647
That's the one person
who wasn't there.

12:26.648 --> 12:28.440
But is mentioned.
We could lean on him.

12:28.441 --> 12:30.440
Nineteen.

12:30.441 --> 12:32.814
And you could.
If you knew who he was.

12:32.815 --> 12:34.398
Can you give me a hint?

12:34.399 --> 12:36.564
We are not fucking playing
Password, Bryan.

12:36.565 --> 12:38.606
This is for your good.

12:38.607 --> 12:41.190
For my good.

12:41.191 --> 12:43.856
For fucking good,
you know?

12:43.857 --> 12:46.772
♪ mid-tempo music ♪

12:46.773 --> 12:51.772
♪♪♪

12:51.773 --> 12:56.772
♪♪♪

12:56.773 --> 13:01.731
♪♪♪

13:01.732 --> 13:03.981
'Becca, Wendy!

13:03.982 --> 13:05.148
- Hi, Mark.
- Cubes!

13:05.149 --> 13:07.190
I'm so fired up that
you made it up here.

13:07.191 --> 13:08.898
This is gonna be
so much fun.

13:08.899 --> 13:10.564
Wait till you get to ride
on these things.

13:10.565 --> 13:12.731
The power is incredible.

13:12.732 --> 13:14.440
Anyways,
this is my guy Phil.

13:14.441 --> 13:16.981
He's gonna train you up and
make sure you have a good time.

13:16.982 --> 13:18.148
Place is all yours.

13:18.149 --> 13:20.064
Thanks.
Can't wait.

13:20.065 --> 13:23.356
♪ dramatic music ♪

13:23.357 --> 13:25.106
...Sooooo, my Daddy,

13:25.107 --> 13:27.148
and I know you'd think
I called him father,

13:27.149 --> 13:28.898
but he was Daddy
and Mommy was--

13:28.899 --> 13:31.148
Mommy?
She sure was.

13:31.149 --> 13:34.190
What Daddy said was:
elbow grease alone

13:34.191 --> 13:37.772
won't solve what elbow grease
and a few silver coins will.

13:37.773 --> 13:39.522
A real philosopher king.

13:39.523 --> 13:41.898
He also told me to find a career
that would justify

13:41.899 --> 13:43.522
elbow patches
on my sport coats.

13:43.523 --> 13:47.064
"Because that would signify
useful work, Pa?" I asked.

13:47.065 --> 13:49.023
Pa, now?
Pa. Yes.

13:49.024 --> 13:50.898
And he said: no, Son,

13:50.899 --> 13:52.939
because folks will believe
you mean well.

13:52.940 --> 13:54.731
All this to say...

13:54.732 --> 13:56.315
Her trouble
won't go away

13:56.316 --> 13:58.231
because we smile nice
and ask even nicer.

13:58.232 --> 14:01.522
It's gonna take some
institutional lubricant.

14:01.523 --> 14:02.772
How much.

14:02.773 --> 14:03.814
$25 million.

14:03.815 --> 14:06.398
Ouch.
Now I think I need the lube.

14:06.399 --> 14:08.024
But fine. Do it.

14:10.274 --> 14:13.564
Hey, Ayles, you actually
even know your father?

14:13.565 --> 14:15.565
Does anyone, really?

14:17.191 --> 14:18.481
How was breakfast?

14:18.482 --> 14:20.522
Eh. Went well...

14:20.523 --> 14:23.564
Listen, I want you to
stay on this with Ayles.

14:23.565 --> 14:26.398
Make sure it happens.
Never let her know we did it.

14:26.399 --> 14:28.440
That might be hard.
These places like to advertise.

14:28.441 --> 14:30.731
Try. I don't want her
to feel beholden.

14:30.732 --> 14:32.564
You are that rarest
of creatures.

14:32.565 --> 14:34.772
An actual gentleman.

14:34.773 --> 14:37.689
Basically,
just for her.

14:37.690 --> 14:39.939
But yeah.

14:39.940 --> 14:43.398
♪ dramatic music ♪

14:43.399 --> 14:44.939
♪♪♪

14:44.940 --> 14:46.606
[Senior] ...You mean
about the idiot

14:46.607 --> 14:48.898
[Senior] who stands to lose
the most? Can I really--

14:48.899 --> 14:50.106
[static hisses]

14:50.107 --> 14:51.606
[key clacks]

14:51.607 --> 14:53.564
[Senior] ...You mean
about the idiot

14:53.565 --> 14:55.564
[Senior] who stands to lose
the most? Can I really--

14:55.565 --> 14:57.731
[static hisses]
Fuck.

14:57.732 --> 14:59.315
[sighs]

14:59.316 --> 15:03.064
♪♪♪

15:03.065 --> 15:04.772
[keypad clicks]

15:04.773 --> 15:06.606
♪♪♪

15:06.607 --> 15:10.190
Jock, I need
some warrants...

15:10.191 --> 15:11.898
No. No,
Funt won't grant these.

15:11.899 --> 15:14.689
I need your, uh, friendly judge.

15:14.690 --> 15:17.064
Yeah.

15:17.065 --> 15:18.814
[phone hangs up]

15:18.815 --> 15:21.023
♪♪♪

15:21.024 --> 15:22.772
[key clacks]

15:22.773 --> 15:24.939
♪♪♪

15:24.940 --> 15:27.315
Now, we can talk in here.
It's been swept.

15:27.316 --> 15:28.981
The fridge is stocked
and I can order--

15:28.982 --> 15:30.440
--Let's not do
the whole service thing.

15:30.441 --> 15:32.731
No food. No drink.
We'll make it quick.

15:32.732 --> 15:34.273
Sure.
Pit stop at Le Mans,

15:34.274 --> 15:36.273
tires, oil,
back out of the chute.

15:36.274 --> 15:38.064
Not a long night of necking
at the drive in.

15:38.065 --> 15:39.481
Definitely not.
Yeah.

15:39.482 --> 15:40.981
No.
Here's the thing:

15:40.982 --> 15:44.356
last time we sat here
we talked about revenge.

15:44.357 --> 15:46.398
And how we were to help
each other achieve it.

15:46.399 --> 15:49.064
And we have and will
continue to--

15:49.065 --> 15:50.231
About that.

15:50.232 --> 15:52.647
Look, I got Taylor
in the well,

15:52.648 --> 15:54.856
it has applied the lotion
from the basket.

15:54.857 --> 15:56.647
All that's left
is the skinning.

15:56.648 --> 15:59.814
Which is to say: they will
soon be hemorrhaging money,

15:59.815 --> 16:02.315
vulnerable, desperate and ready
to make the kind of move

16:02.316 --> 16:04.190
that will make your job
very easy.

16:04.191 --> 16:06.689
You're always telling me
how simple my gig is.

16:06.690 --> 16:08.814
If it's all so basic,
why don't you do the skinning?

16:08.815 --> 16:11.731
I'll tell you: because
it's bloody work. Grimy.

16:11.732 --> 16:14.481
Then roll 'em up and sink 'em in
up to the shoulders.

16:14.482 --> 16:16.689
Oh, is that an order?
It's shorthand.

16:16.690 --> 16:18.856
But if you need me to curtsy
and bow, just say the word.

16:18.857 --> 16:20.481
It's one or the other.
Not both.

16:20.482 --> 16:24.398
And no. What I need is your
expertise to do it right.

16:24.399 --> 16:27.190
I set people up all the time,
but to do it

16:27.191 --> 16:29.689
without opening up an
entrapment charge is difficult.

16:29.690 --> 16:32.106
The right trap
has to come from you.

16:32.107 --> 16:33.731
If Taylor is floundering
and desperate,

16:33.732 --> 16:36.064
you know better than me
what their next move will be.

16:36.065 --> 16:38.481
What might tempt them
to take a chance?

16:38.482 --> 16:40.356
The answer to
all their problems.

16:40.357 --> 16:43.315
Yes.
And then, we dangle that.

16:43.316 --> 16:45.564
Now, uh,
a corrupt associate.

16:45.565 --> 16:48.647
Weak former employee?
Someone you've let go.

16:48.648 --> 16:50.231
Offering funds
or a service

16:50.232 --> 16:52.106
or an opportunity
too good to pass up...

16:52.107 --> 16:56.898
♪ dramatic music ♪

16:56.899 --> 16:59.814
I know just the fella.

16:59.815 --> 17:01.898
Something about the directness
of the metaphor here

17:01.899 --> 17:03.481
is going to feel absurd
for a minute.

17:03.482 --> 17:05.064
I need you to
fight that off.

17:05.065 --> 17:08.564
And own the fact that you are
moving the fucking earth.

17:08.565 --> 17:11.732
Because that's what you are and
what you do in the actual world.

17:13.148 --> 17:16.022
♪ White Reaper's "Tell Me" ♪

17:16.023 --> 17:19.397
♪♪♪

17:19.398 --> 17:23.689
♪ He likes to roll ♪

17:23.690 --> 17:27.106
♪ In a brand new
stretch-type limo ♪

17:27.107 --> 17:29.731
♪♪♪

17:29.732 --> 17:32.939
♪ And soak up the gold ♪

17:32.940 --> 17:35.814
♪ From all the tickets
and the tees that he's sold ♪

17:35.815 --> 17:37.606
Yes!

17:37.607 --> 17:38.607
♪♪♪

17:38.608 --> 17:41.106
Ah!

17:41.107 --> 17:43.939
You were fucking right.
We moved earth.

17:43.940 --> 17:46.522
We were destruction.

17:46.523 --> 17:48.939
Elemental.
No gray area.

17:48.940 --> 17:50.398
Being in the cockpit
was like

17:50.399 --> 17:52.190
hitting the stage
with The Clash.

17:52.191 --> 17:54.440
You had to be totally present
to deal with it.

17:54.441 --> 17:55.814
Got me right out
of my head.

17:55.815 --> 17:57.772
I figured it would work better
than a day spa.

17:57.773 --> 17:59.772
Thank you
for taking the time.

17:59.773 --> 18:01.772
I needed the reset, too.

18:01.773 --> 18:04.647
Though I probably don't have to
tell you what I need.

18:04.648 --> 18:08.190
You already know in what--
five minutes with someone?

18:08.191 --> 18:10.772
Truth:
Mm-hmm.

18:10.773 --> 18:12.772
I'd love to work with you,

18:12.773 --> 18:15.190
but you don't need much that
you don't already give yourself.

18:15.191 --> 18:16.814
That's what
sets you apart.

18:16.815 --> 18:19.440
Most people let their
childhood bullshit run them.

18:19.441 --> 18:21.064
You use yours
to propel you.

18:21.065 --> 18:23.231
And not in a way that
you're hiding from it, either,

18:23.232 --> 18:25.064
and it's gonna bite you.

18:25.065 --> 18:26.481
You synthesize it.

18:26.482 --> 18:28.981
Like you do information
about companies.

18:28.982 --> 18:31.481
You're doing exactly what
you're meant to be doing.

18:31.482 --> 18:33.231
That was amazing.

18:33.232 --> 18:35.315
And you know it.

18:35.316 --> 18:36.814
And you get off on it.

18:36.815 --> 18:39.606
Well, I'm doing what
I'm meant to be doing, too.

18:39.607 --> 18:41.440
You ever want to be
out on your own?

18:41.441 --> 18:42.647
Have your own practice?

18:42.648 --> 18:44.440
I've thought about it
from time to time.

18:44.441 --> 18:46.814
But I'm in the right place.
Which is a good thing,

18:46.815 --> 18:48.981
because if I was out on my own,
this Med Board thing

18:48.982 --> 18:50.981
would be putting me
right out of business.

18:50.982 --> 18:52.814
How are you
handling it?

18:52.815 --> 18:55.772
One thing that's come
from this year:

18:55.773 --> 18:58.273
I know I can handle
fucking anything.

18:58.274 --> 19:01.023
And Axe Cap, it's mine.

19:01.024 --> 19:05.856
They really rallied around
me--in their own weird way.

19:05.857 --> 19:08.064
That's the upside of being
on a team, I guess.

19:08.065 --> 19:09.689
I can see that.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.106
It's just not how I work.

19:11.107 --> 19:12.731
[inhales deeply]

19:12.732 --> 19:14.064
I like owning a team.

19:14.065 --> 19:16.190
[both laugh]

19:16.191 --> 19:18.148
Should we hit it?

19:18.149 --> 19:20.190
[country music playing on radio]

19:20.191 --> 19:22.564
You've had a few,
you sure you're alright?

19:22.565 --> 19:24.522
We can drive you back
to your hotel--

19:24.523 --> 19:27.647
Oh. Don't worry,
we're not driving.

19:27.648 --> 19:29.815
[helicopter blades whirring]

19:38.399 --> 19:41.564
♪ dramatic music ♪

19:41.565 --> 19:43.522
♪♪♪

19:43.523 --> 19:45.898
You're not going
for 20 are you?

19:45.899 --> 19:48.689
Nope.
I went about this another way.

19:48.690 --> 19:50.939
And you were right, and we are
going to get them all.

19:50.940 --> 19:54.356
Sounds like somebody did some
old fashioned prosecutor work.

19:54.357 --> 19:57.772
I figure, I'm behind the desk,
maybe I should do the job.

19:57.773 --> 20:00.273
So I did the job. And got
some warrants and subpoenas.

20:00.274 --> 20:01.939
And you are going to
execute same.

20:01.940 --> 20:03.481
On?

20:03.482 --> 20:05.481
The sitting Secretary of
the Treasury, Todd Krakow

20:05.482 --> 20:07.356
and the safe
of the father of

20:07.357 --> 20:09.689
the sitting Attorney General
for the State of New York.

20:09.690 --> 20:12.481
You will go, yourself,
to handle it.

20:12.482 --> 20:14.898
Bring good agents
with you.

20:14.899 --> 20:17.398
These are
the warrants.

20:17.399 --> 20:19.522
♪ dramatic music ♪

20:19.523 --> 20:20.772
And I'm on my way.

20:20.773 --> 20:25.398
♪♪♪

20:25.399 --> 20:28.606
[indistinct conversations]

20:28.607 --> 20:30.981
Hello everybody...

20:30.982 --> 20:32.441
[conversations stop]

20:33.773 --> 20:38.273
Sanford, surprised
to see you here.

20:38.274 --> 20:40.898
You passed on a board seat
when it was offered.

20:40.899 --> 20:42.106
I did.

20:42.107 --> 20:43.522
But I have a real
vested interest

20:43.523 --> 20:45.856
in how this meeting goes.

20:45.857 --> 20:47.772
Uh...

20:47.773 --> 20:49.898
Alright, people.

20:49.899 --> 20:52.231
Big announcement,
big acquisition.

20:52.232 --> 20:53.606
Of Kling Appliances.

20:53.607 --> 20:54.981
We have taken ownership
of the company

20:54.982 --> 20:56.856
and will go back to
rolling out their product.

20:56.857 --> 20:58.606
Now, this strategic
partnership--

20:58.607 --> 21:01.273
We are not going to
sell Kling products.

21:01.274 --> 21:04.772
We will be using Kling to
move toward profitability

21:04.773 --> 21:06.481
in a wholly
different way now.

21:06.482 --> 21:08.647
♪ dramatic music ♪

21:08.648 --> 21:10.481
[Bensinger] Thank you.

21:10.482 --> 21:14.315
Even I don't usually have
an Iron Chef make my pancakes.

21:14.316 --> 21:15.772
All you have to do
is ask...

21:15.773 --> 21:17.023
And send the plane.

21:17.024 --> 21:20.315
[both laugh]
Thanks for this, Alex.

21:20.316 --> 21:22.273
♪♪♪

21:22.274 --> 21:25.106
Mm.

21:25.107 --> 21:28.481
When a man puts on a show
like this, it's rarely--

21:28.482 --> 21:30.106
That's true. But also,

21:30.107 --> 21:33.481
if we're gonna have to have
this conversation, and we are,

21:33.482 --> 21:35.731
we might as well have
something this good.

21:35.732 --> 21:38.898
Well,
it's in our mouths now.

21:38.899 --> 21:40.564
So--

21:40.565 --> 21:42.522
[silverware clatters]

21:42.523 --> 21:44.689
Saler's is
a sinking ship.

21:44.690 --> 21:46.856
But I know how to get
the chest of gold

21:46.857 --> 21:48.731
before it hits
the ocean floor.

21:48.732 --> 21:50.856
You would do that
to Rebecca?

21:50.857 --> 21:53.106
For Rebecca.

21:53.107 --> 21:54.606
It's helping her.

21:54.607 --> 21:57.689
What I didn't realize,
but see now,

21:57.690 --> 21:59.898
is that she made
the one sin that every

21:59.899 --> 22:02.481
private equity investor knows
they can never make.

22:02.482 --> 22:03.814
And it happened
because she is

22:03.815 --> 22:06.689
as kind-hearted and good
as she is smart.

22:06.690 --> 22:08.731
And that is--
Cares too much.

22:08.732 --> 22:10.814
About this one
in particular.

22:10.815 --> 22:12.981
Mm. It's a suicide play
at this point.

22:12.982 --> 22:15.023
She's lashed herself
to the side of this thing

22:15.024 --> 22:17.356
and refuses to jump off.

22:17.357 --> 22:19.606
We won't just be
saving ourselves.

22:19.607 --> 22:22.023
We'll also be saving her.

22:22.024 --> 22:25.898
Yeah.
I guess we will be.

22:25.899 --> 22:28.772
You okay with it?

22:28.773 --> 22:31.398
With getting the gold
and doing the right thing?

22:31.399 --> 22:33.772
♪♪♪

22:33.773 --> 22:36.064
Yes I am.

22:36.065 --> 22:37.689
Now please
pass the syrup.

22:37.690 --> 22:39.440
These fucking things
are delightful.

22:39.441 --> 22:42.564
[chuckles]

22:42.565 --> 22:45.564
[Axe] All Saler's locations
will be closed,

22:45.565 --> 22:47.898
[Axe] effective
immediately.

22:47.899 --> 22:49.898
The real estate
will be transferred

22:49.899 --> 22:51.689
to a real estate
investment trust,

22:51.690 --> 22:53.814
controlled by
Sanford Bensinger--and me--

22:53.815 --> 22:56.273
where it will eventually be
sold off at market value.

22:56.274 --> 22:58.564
[Axe] The clothing brands,
home goods,

22:58.565 --> 23:00.606
[Axe] Treads For Tots shoe line,
Maker Man Tools,

23:00.607 --> 23:03.190
[Axe] and the auto parts brand
will all be spun off

23:03.191 --> 23:07.731
for top dollar to private equity
buyers who've been lined up.

23:07.732 --> 23:09.981
Further, Saler's debt
will be dumped

23:09.982 --> 23:11.522
onto Kling's balance sheet

23:11.523 --> 23:13.398
[Axe] and that company
will then be put into

23:13.399 --> 23:17.481
Chapter 11 bankruptcy
effective immediately.

23:17.482 --> 23:21.731
Cute pitch,
but I wonder

23:21.732 --> 23:26.440
how the fuck
do you think

23:26.441 --> 23:30.398
you have the authority
to do that when I'm CEO.

23:30.399 --> 23:32.273
[sighs]

23:32.274 --> 23:34.606
Well, young lady,
unfortunately,

23:34.607 --> 23:37.939
if you don't ratify the plan,
you'll be removed.

23:37.940 --> 23:41.647
I've converted my debt to shares
with voting rights.

23:41.648 --> 23:42.772
When?

23:42.773 --> 23:45.106
Yesterday.
[Axe] So his shares,

23:45.107 --> 23:47.148
[Axe] along with mine and
everyone else in this room,

23:47.149 --> 23:48.564
make up the majority.

23:48.565 --> 23:49.981
You can't stop it.

23:49.982 --> 23:52.647
What about
the 50,000 employees?

23:52.648 --> 23:55.273
Well, we'll settle out their
pension plans and benefits.

23:55.274 --> 23:57.315
For a fraction of
what they're owed.

23:57.316 --> 24:01.856
I know people, and what
those people will feel is:

24:01.857 --> 24:03.481
something's better
than nothing.

24:03.482 --> 24:08.231
And you--you assholes--
you're gonna go along with this?

24:08.232 --> 24:10.731
♪ dramatic music ♪

24:10.732 --> 24:12.231
Ugh.
How could you?

24:12.232 --> 24:14.564
[Axe] Oh. They already did.
The board voted.

24:14.565 --> 24:17.398
Or gave me their proxies.
Same thing.

24:17.399 --> 24:20.273
It's because every
shareholder will get

24:20.274 --> 24:23.689
a massive one time windfall
dividend payment.

24:23.690 --> 24:25.273
And then we can all go
our separate ways.

24:25.274 --> 24:27.481
Keith, how many shares
do you hold?

24:27.482 --> 24:28.856
Thirty-three thousand.

24:28.857 --> 24:30.898
Well, congratulations,
Keith.

24:30.899 --> 24:33.398
You just graduated from
300 grand in a bad stock

24:33.399 --> 24:36.440
to thirty-three million
in cash.

24:36.441 --> 24:38.023
Rebecca,
you could be making

24:38.024 --> 24:40.190
close to a billion
on this transaction.

24:40.191 --> 24:43.647
Miss Cantu,

24:43.648 --> 24:46.522
I know how this stings.

24:46.523 --> 24:48.814
I had my paper route
stolen from me

24:48.815 --> 24:51.273
after I'd built it up
to cover the entire city.

24:51.274 --> 24:53.481
[Bensinger] Damn newspaper
took it in-house.

24:53.482 --> 24:55.689
I felt steamed

24:55.690 --> 24:58.356
'til I bought the whole thing
and sold it to a chain.

24:58.357 --> 25:00.190
Oracular wisdom
feels better

25:00.191 --> 25:04.149
when the oracle hasn't just
anally rended you.

25:05.523 --> 25:09.898
Gentlemen, ladies, why don't we
go work out the myriad details

25:09.899 --> 25:12.231
in the back office
and give them the room.

25:12.232 --> 25:13.856
[door opens]

25:13.857 --> 25:17.023
[indistinct conversations]

25:17.024 --> 25:18.981
[door closes]

25:18.982 --> 25:23.065
You snake motherfucker.

25:24.773 --> 25:27.898
You sent me off
and you set me up--

25:27.899 --> 25:32.148
Your way was an arduous five
year, capital-intensive crawl.

25:32.149 --> 25:34.106
Now you've just cleared
over a billion

25:34.107 --> 25:36.148
in a few months' time.

25:36.149 --> 25:38.356
It isn't about that for me
and you know it.

25:38.357 --> 25:42.231
I want to run this business
for real.

25:42.232 --> 25:44.564
This one
wasn't fit to run.

25:44.565 --> 25:47.231
You can build it back up
from the ground, better,

25:47.232 --> 25:50.606
without the negative drag
of toxic fucking debt,

25:50.607 --> 25:51.856
if you really want.

25:51.857 --> 25:53.273
When did you
land on your plan

25:53.274 --> 25:56.106
to liquidate the company
out from under me, hmm--

25:56.107 --> 26:00.231
was it the first time
that I told you about it?

26:00.232 --> 26:02.064
No.

26:02.065 --> 26:04.898
No, it was much closer to
when you climbed into bed

26:04.899 --> 26:07.939
and made a fucking pact
with my sworn enemy.

26:07.940 --> 26:10.689
But, hey,
as you once told me,

26:10.690 --> 26:12.689
you'll come to see
the wisdom in this plan.

26:12.690 --> 26:13.898
You already do--

26:13.899 --> 26:16.190
Oh. Fuck you.
We're done.

26:16.191 --> 26:18.231
[Axe] Well, you should
think fondly of me

26:18.232 --> 26:20.939
when the Street calls you
a genius--for this plan--

26:20.940 --> 26:23.231
as you approach
your next venture.

26:23.232 --> 26:27.522
I need to know
what you told yourself.

26:27.523 --> 26:31.315
♪ dramatic music ♪

26:31.316 --> 26:34.981
[Axe] I wanted
to let it go--

26:34.982 --> 26:36.939
[Axe] what you did

26:36.940 --> 26:39.981
[Axe] by making that deal
with Taylor.

26:39.982 --> 26:42.689
[Axe] I wanted to think of it
the way you said:

26:42.690 --> 26:44.814
[Axe] not as disloyal.

26:44.815 --> 26:47.647
[Axe] Or an action
against me.

26:47.648 --> 26:51.231
[Axe] But as a practical
solution to a problem

26:51.232 --> 26:55.148
[Axe] that you-- someone
I loved-- was faced with.

26:55.149 --> 26:58.148
[Axe] And so that night,
I told you it was fine.

26:58.149 --> 27:01.148
[Axe] And I wanted it
to be true.

27:01.149 --> 27:04.190
[Axe] I laid there in bed
next to you,

27:04.191 --> 27:06.814
[Axe] and I just tried to
breathe out the bad,

27:06.815 --> 27:08.689
[Axe] breathe in the good.

27:08.690 --> 27:10.481
[Axe] But with each breath,

27:10.482 --> 27:14.481
[Axe] instead of peace, love and
understanding filling my lungs,

27:14.482 --> 27:18.522
[Axe] the old bile was there.

27:18.523 --> 27:22.898
[Axe] I stared at the ceiling,

27:22.899 --> 27:27.939
[Axe] with you sleeping next to
me-- beautiful and serene,

27:27.940 --> 27:31.981
[Axe] and I played out
our relationship to its end.

27:31.982 --> 27:35.190
♪♪♪

27:35.191 --> 27:37.440
[Axe] I thought
about marriage.

27:37.441 --> 27:40.522
[Axe] Let it land for me
that it actually was

27:40.523 --> 27:43.481
[Axe] something I'd already
assumed was going to happen.

27:43.482 --> 27:46.023
[Axe] Us having kids
together, too.

27:46.024 --> 27:47.772
[Axe] I smiled at the notion.

27:47.773 --> 27:49.356
[Axe] It was hopeful.

27:49.357 --> 27:51.522
[Axe] Romantic.

27:51.523 --> 27:54.564
[Axe] The kind of thought
a normal man would be having.

27:54.565 --> 27:56.356
♪♪♪

27:56.357 --> 27:59.772
But then,

27:59.773 --> 28:03.731
I felt something
go cold in me.

28:03.732 --> 28:06.898
And I knew the truth
was in that cold.

28:06.899 --> 28:08.315
♪♪♪

28:08.316 --> 28:10.814
And that eventually,
it would turn hot.

28:10.815 --> 28:12.898
To rage.
And when it did,

28:12.899 --> 28:15.440
[Axe] I would blow
the whole fucking thing up,

28:15.441 --> 28:16.939
[Axe] kids and all.

28:16.940 --> 28:20.398
'Cause, sure,
your choice was rational.

28:20.399 --> 28:24.106
But to me,
it was traitorous.

28:24.107 --> 28:25.981
And I wouldn't be able
to live with it.

28:25.982 --> 28:27.564
I'd wreck everything
we had over it.

28:27.565 --> 28:30.356
[Axe] I would make you
suffer tenfold

28:30.357 --> 28:32.148
[Axe] for what
I had suffered.

28:32.149 --> 28:35.064
[Axe] Especially if I waited,
without crushing Taylor.

28:35.065 --> 28:38.981
[Axe] Because by then,
Taylor would be rich and safe.

28:38.982 --> 28:43.356
[Axe] So I decided:
fuck it.

28:43.357 --> 28:44.772
[sighs]

28:44.773 --> 28:46.772
[Axe] Might as well
get my revenge

28:46.773 --> 28:48.481
and rip the scab off
this fucking thing

28:48.482 --> 28:51.731
between us
at the same time.

28:51.732 --> 28:53.440
♪♪♪

28:53.441 --> 28:55.689
Then we'd be even, too.

28:55.690 --> 28:58.606
Each fucked over.

28:58.607 --> 29:01.064
Each aware of who
the other really is.

29:01.065 --> 29:04.772
♪♪♪

29:04.773 --> 29:08.522
Then...

29:08.523 --> 29:12.273
Then we could find out
what was still between us.

29:12.274 --> 29:15.231
♪♪♪

29:15.232 --> 29:19.772
What's between us now
is nothing.

29:19.773 --> 29:23.981
♪♪♪

29:23.982 --> 29:28.106
♪♪♪

29:28.107 --> 29:29.689
[door closes]

29:29.690 --> 29:32.647
♪♪♪

29:32.648 --> 29:35.356
♪♪♪

29:35.357 --> 29:37.939
[Hammon] Bobby Axelrod
has control of Saler's.

29:37.940 --> 29:39.231
Rebecca is out.

29:39.232 --> 29:40.815
He's putting Kling
into bankruptcy.

29:43.149 --> 29:45.981
Our equity will be wiped out.
Our position will go to zero.

29:45.982 --> 29:47.814
Our firm will lose
three quarters of a billion,

29:47.815 --> 29:49.231
maybe a little more.

29:49.232 --> 29:50.481
When news of that
gets out,

29:50.482 --> 29:51.898
we may not have a firm.

29:51.899 --> 29:53.647
I can have Lauren get
to the investors first,

29:53.648 --> 29:55.898
try to gain a vote of--
I wouldn't give me that vote,

29:55.899 --> 29:57.564
they won't either. No.

29:57.565 --> 29:59.814
What if we go Doug Flutie style,
toss a literal Hail Mary?

29:59.815 --> 30:01.647
Just make a huge bet,
on, like, four names.

30:01.648 --> 30:02.939
Double up or bomb out.

30:02.940 --> 30:04.481
I'd like to work in
this business again.

30:04.482 --> 30:07.023
So, yeah. No.
Fuck. We need time...

30:07.024 --> 30:10.231
♪ dramatic music ♪

30:10.232 --> 30:12.898
I might have something.
A text I got earlier.

30:12.899 --> 30:14.647
♪♪♪

30:14.648 --> 30:17.398
Mafee, we're going to a meeting
with a friend of yours.

30:17.399 --> 30:20.023
[door opens]

30:20.024 --> 30:22.148
♪♪♪

30:22.149 --> 30:24.231
Mm.
Seems I missed the party.

30:24.232 --> 30:26.689
Taylor's P&L's
been crippled.

30:26.690 --> 30:28.898
They're ripe to make
that desperate move.

30:28.899 --> 30:32.273
I thought
I smelled blood.

30:32.274 --> 30:33.564
Everything's in place
on my end.

30:33.565 --> 30:36.148
Good.
One more thing though.

30:36.149 --> 30:38.689
I want you to arrest
but NOT charge Taylor.

30:38.690 --> 30:42.356
[chuckles]
After everything I've done,

30:42.357 --> 30:46.148
all the plans I've laid in,
why would I do that?

30:46.149 --> 30:47.606
Because it's what I want.

30:47.607 --> 30:50.939
And 'cause I want Taylor back at
Axe Capital, working for me.

30:50.940 --> 30:52.731
Come again?

30:52.732 --> 30:55.398
They're the best player
I've seen in this league

30:55.399 --> 30:58.106
in two decades.
Real five-tool, you know?

30:58.107 --> 31:01.772
Back at the beginning
this was advertised as

31:01.773 --> 31:03.356
me getting
a Wall Street scalp.

31:03.357 --> 31:06.356
But now that it's haircut time,
you tell me no.

31:06.357 --> 31:08.106
Why don't you just
hire the kid back

31:08.107 --> 31:10.148
and stop wasting
my fucking time?

31:10.149 --> 31:11.606
'Cause they won't
come for money.

31:11.607 --> 31:13.440
But they will
come from fear.

31:13.441 --> 31:17.522
And from leverage.
So leverage them and scare them.

31:17.523 --> 31:21.398
And if anyone's been
wasting fucking time here...

31:21.399 --> 31:23.440
♪ dramatic music ♪

31:23.441 --> 31:27.814
♪♪♪

31:27.815 --> 31:32.565
♪♪♪

31:35.732 --> 31:36.690
[keys clacking]

31:36.691 --> 31:38.773
[cellphone vibrating]

31:42.565 --> 31:44.106
Hello?

31:44.107 --> 31:46.231
[Dr. Zhang] Dr. Rhoades.
I am pleased to tell you

31:46.232 --> 31:48.106
that the Medical Board
has taken into account

31:48.107 --> 31:49.981
the fact that you
willingly came forward.

31:49.982 --> 31:52.106
And that you could have
easily lied.

31:52.107 --> 31:54.814
Really.

31:54.815 --> 31:58.772
[Dr. Zhang] Yes. It showed that
you are already making changes.

31:58.773 --> 32:01.106
[Dr. Zhang] And that you are,
at core, a doctor who cares.

32:01.107 --> 32:02.939
[Dr. Zhang] We have also
been provided with

32:02.940 --> 32:04.939
[Dr. Zhang] dozens of letters
to your character.

32:04.940 --> 32:07.356
[Dr. Zhang] And that highlight
how much you have given

32:07.357 --> 32:09.106
[Dr. Zhang] of your time
over the years

32:09.107 --> 32:10.856
[Dr. Zhang] to those
less fortunate.

32:10.857 --> 32:15.190
So we've decided to set aside
the findings of the proceeding.

32:15.191 --> 32:17.148
And to give you
a verbal warning instead.

32:17.149 --> 32:20.522
[Dr. Zhang] Consider that given,
and the matter concluded.

32:20.523 --> 32:23.315
♪♪♪

32:23.316 --> 32:25.689
Thank you, Dr. Zhang.

32:25.690 --> 32:28.440
♪♪♪

32:28.441 --> 32:30.231
[exhales sharply]

32:30.232 --> 32:31.856
Yeah. I'm just finishing up
a few things,

32:31.857 --> 32:34.023
you can head out
for the night.

32:34.024 --> 32:36.981
♪♪♪

32:36.982 --> 32:38.148
[door opens]

32:38.149 --> 32:39.149
[sighs]

32:39.150 --> 32:40.190
[door closes]

32:40.191 --> 32:42.148
[sniffs]

32:42.149 --> 32:43.981
[cellphone whooshes]

32:43.982 --> 32:46.522
♪♪♪

32:46.523 --> 32:48.315
[cellphone whooshes]

32:48.316 --> 32:51.356
♪ dramatic music ♪

32:51.357 --> 32:55.356
♪♪♪

32:55.357 --> 32:59.273
♪♪♪

32:59.274 --> 33:00.898
[drawer closes]

33:00.899 --> 33:04.315
♪♪♪

33:04.316 --> 33:07.856
♪♪♪

33:07.857 --> 33:11.190
♪♪♪

33:11.191 --> 33:13.522
[door closes]

33:13.523 --> 33:16.398
♪♪♪

33:16.399 --> 33:19.356
♪♪♪

33:19.357 --> 33:20.856
[keys jangle]

33:20.857 --> 33:25.064
♪♪♪

33:25.065 --> 33:29.315
♪♪♪

33:29.316 --> 33:33.440
♪♪♪

33:33.441 --> 33:37.689
♪♪♪

33:37.690 --> 33:41.856
♪♪♪

33:41.857 --> 33:43.898
[lock disengages]

33:43.899 --> 33:48.564
♪♪♪

33:48.565 --> 33:53.231
♪♪♪

33:53.232 --> 33:57.939
♪♪♪

33:57.940 --> 34:02.898
♪♪♪

34:02.899 --> 34:07.564
♪♪♪

34:07.565 --> 34:12.231
♪♪♪

34:12.232 --> 34:16.938
♪♪♪

34:16.940 --> 34:21.898
♪♪♪

34:21.899 --> 34:26.606
♪♪♪

34:26.607 --> 34:31.190
♪♪♪

34:31.190 --> 34:33.731
[audio fast-forwarding]

34:33.732 --> 34:35.856
[Senior] ...You mean
about the idiot

34:35.857 --> 34:38.063
[Senior] who stands to lose
the most? Can I really--

34:38.065 --> 34:39.898
[Ira] Yes.
I can't listen to future plans.

34:39.899 --> 34:41.856
[Ira] But the things
you've already done.

34:41.857 --> 34:43.772
[Ira] And the people with whom
you've done 'em,

34:43.773 --> 34:45.647
[Ira] that I need to know.

34:45.648 --> 34:48.522
[Chuck] Go ahead. Press on.
Privilege was clearly in place.

34:48.523 --> 34:51.688
[Senior] Once I tell you who
he is, Ira, we can't go back.

34:51.690 --> 34:53.688
[Senior] It's a real mindblower.

34:53.690 --> 34:56.315
[Chuck] We should all brace
ourselves for what's coming.

34:56.315 --> 34:58.606
[Chuck] Yes.

34:58.607 --> 35:01.398
[Chuck] Well. Do it, Dad.
Say the name.

35:01.399 --> 35:05.106
Well, I mean, at this point
it's gotta be clear, right?

35:05.107 --> 35:07.190
♪♪♪

35:07.191 --> 35:11.190
The idiot in question
is Bryan Connerty.

35:11.191 --> 35:12.981
[Chuck] Yes. Well.
The rub of it is.

35:12.982 --> 35:15.106
[Chuck] If Connerty is
listening right now,

35:15.107 --> 35:17.356
[Chuck] it means he's crossed
all legal and ethical bounds

35:17.357 --> 35:19.772
[Chuck] and our little plan
is about to bear fruit...

35:19.773 --> 35:21.856
[Chuck] But, uh [chuckles]
you're not listening,

35:21.857 --> 35:23.522
are you, Bryan?

35:23.523 --> 35:25.772
'Cause you don't
break the law.

35:25.773 --> 35:28.689
[Chuck] But, if he is
"headphones on" right now,

35:28.690 --> 35:30.939
[Chuck] it means he's gone
completely over the line

35:30.940 --> 35:33.689
[Chuck] and committed all manner
of crimes that led to this,

35:33.690 --> 35:36.856
and his arrest is, uh,
moments away.

35:36.857 --> 35:39.606
Which is why we dubbed
the man 'the idiot'.

35:39.607 --> 35:41.398
Should've called him
the fucking idiot--

35:41.399 --> 35:44.481
♪ dramatic music ♪

35:44.482 --> 35:48.731
♪♪♪

35:48.732 --> 35:53.023
♪♪♪

35:53.024 --> 35:55.939
Ah, fuck.

35:55.940 --> 35:58.689
You should probably
say it again. Louder.

35:58.690 --> 36:00.356
Cuz yeah.
You are fucked.

36:00.357 --> 36:02.481
Let's go.

36:02.482 --> 36:05.357
♪♪♪

36:07.982 --> 36:09.647
Kate--

36:09.648 --> 36:12.064
Bryan, I had them hold you
in here, as a courtesy--

36:12.065 --> 36:13.731
but what the fuck?
I--

36:13.732 --> 36:16.481
[Sacker] You kept asking if
you would understand everything

36:16.482 --> 36:18.522
[Sacker] if you listened
to the tape.

36:18.523 --> 36:19.772
[Sacker] I told you

36:19.773 --> 36:21.648
[Sacker] unfortunately
the answer was yes.

36:23.024 --> 36:24.898
It was my hope you never
found out what came next.

36:24.899 --> 36:27.522
Whatever bullshit they were
running on that recording,

36:27.523 --> 36:29.898
tell me you recovered stuff
from the safes

36:29.899 --> 36:32.731
that will prove this thing
for what it is.

36:32.732 --> 36:34.731
Oh, I got proof
from the safes, Bryan,

36:34.732 --> 36:37.481
[Sacker] but not the kind
you were looking for.

36:37.482 --> 36:40.564
♪ dramatic music ♪

36:40.565 --> 36:45.190
♪♪♪

36:45.191 --> 36:49.939
♪♪♪

36:49.940 --> 36:51.522
This isn't
a contract laying out

36:51.523 --> 36:53.856
your participation in
some real estate scam.

36:53.857 --> 36:56.190
No, but it is
my participation in

36:56.191 --> 36:58.814
a New York State sting operation
targeting certain

36:58.815 --> 37:00.981
corrupt members of
the Department of Justice.

37:00.982 --> 37:02.606
♪♪♪

37:02.607 --> 37:04.315
An overzealous prosecutor--

37:04.316 --> 37:05.981
especially a US Attorney--

37:05.982 --> 37:07.898
is a very dangerous thing...

37:07.899 --> 37:12.606
♪♪♪

37:12.607 --> 37:14.106
And Rhoades Senior?

37:14.107 --> 37:17.106
♪♪♪

37:17.107 --> 37:20.064
♪♪♪

37:20.065 --> 37:22.231
[drill whirs]
Don't ruin my box.

37:22.232 --> 37:25.814
♪♪♪

37:25.815 --> 37:26.898
[keypad beeping]

37:26.899 --> 37:31.772
♪♪♪

37:31.773 --> 37:36.606
♪♪♪

37:36.607 --> 37:41.481
♪♪♪

37:41.482 --> 37:46.356
♪♪♪

37:46.357 --> 37:48.856
It's not what you wanted,
but it is what was there.

37:48.857 --> 37:50.939
♪♪♪

37:50.940 --> 37:52.148
[sighs]

37:52.149 --> 37:56.606
♪♪♪

37:56.607 --> 37:58.814
Sonofabitch...

37:58.815 --> 38:01.481
♪♪♪

38:01.482 --> 38:04.273
[sighs]

38:04.274 --> 38:06.315
May I?

38:06.316 --> 38:09.064
♪♪♪

38:09.065 --> 38:11.982
Keep it brief, we still
have processing to do.

38:14.274 --> 38:16.190
[inhales deeply]

38:16.191 --> 38:18.273
[door closes]

38:18.274 --> 38:21.356
Oh. Bryan, it pains me
to be here like this--

38:21.357 --> 38:23.814
Does it?
But you lined up against me,

38:23.815 --> 38:25.857
and that just
wasn't right.

38:28.690 --> 38:30.731
We could've
worked together.

38:30.732 --> 38:33.856
But you broke ranks
and tried to take me out.

38:33.857 --> 38:36.273
So I had to make
a contingency plan.

38:36.274 --> 38:37.773
[sighs]

38:41.399 --> 38:42.856
How far back?

38:42.857 --> 38:47.064
Well, you know,

38:47.065 --> 38:48.356
pretty far...

38:48.357 --> 38:50.772
This development
is my legacy.

38:50.773 --> 38:53.731
Hell, it's your
legacy too.

38:53.732 --> 38:56.356
Well, I'm glad to see you've got
your legs under you again, Dad.

38:56.357 --> 38:57.898
♪ dramatic music ♪

38:57.899 --> 38:59.898
[sea gulls cry]

38:59.899 --> 39:03.148
♪♪♪

39:03.149 --> 39:06.148
♪♪♪

39:06.149 --> 39:09.023
Dad,

39:09.024 --> 39:12.190
I know how we can
spin this like a top.

39:12.191 --> 39:14.273
We're gonna have to put on
a hell of a show...

39:14.274 --> 39:17.440
But, yeah, this will be
our legacy.

39:17.441 --> 39:19.939
♪♪♪

39:19.940 --> 39:21.856
[Chuck] I knew you'd be
coming after me

39:21.857 --> 39:24.356
[Chuck] and that you'd be up on
me sooner than later...

39:24.357 --> 39:26.315
[Senior]
There's no heat.

39:26.316 --> 39:27.898
[Senior] Sonny, my permits
came back without a hitch...

39:27.899 --> 39:29.731
[Chuck] And of course
I knew that you knew

39:29.732 --> 39:31.315
[Chuck] that Judge DeGiulio
would deny

39:31.316 --> 39:32.689
[Chuck] your wiretap
request...

39:32.690 --> 39:35.231
FBI observed
father and son

39:35.232 --> 39:37.023
on the building site
in question.

39:37.024 --> 39:39.398
You got
a family portrait.

39:39.399 --> 39:42.814
[Chuck] And come to me
with that information.

39:42.815 --> 39:45.315
Connerty came for
a wire on you.

39:45.316 --> 39:47.398
Did you grant it?

39:47.399 --> 39:48.814
I killed it.

39:48.815 --> 39:51.939
[Chuck] And that
you'd be watching.

39:51.940 --> 39:54.023
[Chuck] So we gave you
what you needed

39:54.024 --> 39:55.564
[Chuck] to secure
those wiretaps...

39:55.565 --> 39:58.772
You have your wire.

39:58.773 --> 40:01.356
[Chuck] And I knew you'd do
as I trained you to do,

40:01.357 --> 40:04.606
[Chuck] programmed you almost,
so you'd get on our phones.

40:04.607 --> 40:09.481
I have run into a financing snag
with my development.

40:09.482 --> 40:11.023
What's the problem?

40:11.024 --> 40:14.522
Now, I know you have some
banking contacts these days.

40:14.523 --> 40:16.231
[Chuck] I'll try to help.

40:16.232 --> 40:20.440
[Chuck] So I needed to squeeze
certain players for help.

40:20.441 --> 40:22.981
You're probably wondering how
you're gonna get out of this.

40:22.982 --> 40:24.939
[chuckles] Indeed.
It crossed my mind.

40:24.940 --> 40:27.814
Well, you'll join me
in a greater plan

40:27.815 --> 40:30.148
for the greater good.

40:30.149 --> 40:33.981
♪♪♪

40:33.982 --> 40:36.647
Listening
and loving it...

40:36.648 --> 40:39.939
[Chuck] I needed your boss
fully engaged,

40:39.940 --> 40:41.898
[Chuck] pushing you,
breathing fire down your back.

40:41.899 --> 40:44.814
So once I knew it was
the thing that mattered to him,

40:44.815 --> 40:47.148
I hit the election
angle hard.

40:47.149 --> 40:50.023
By the time I parked
the shit train in his backyard,

40:50.024 --> 40:53.148
both you and Jock were
leaning in so hard,

40:53.149 --> 40:56.148
it was just a question of
playing out an ending for you.

40:56.149 --> 40:59.273
I've taken the liberty.

40:59.274 --> 41:00.898
For our comfort...

41:00.899 --> 41:02.190
[rustling on recorded audio]
What's that rustling?

41:02.191 --> 41:03.772
Did they paper
this fucking deal?

41:03.773 --> 41:05.731
I need to go back to D.C.

41:05.732 --> 41:07.981
I have work to do.

41:07.982 --> 41:10.898
Gentlemen.

41:10.899 --> 41:12.356
[mouths words]

41:12.357 --> 41:15.148
♪♪♪

41:15.149 --> 41:17.772
[Chuck] I've got to admit that
I was a little surprised

41:17.773 --> 41:20.522
by how eager you were
for the dirty tricks

41:20.523 --> 41:22.856
and even crime.

41:22.857 --> 41:26.190
It's the power, of the office,
that gets you leaning forward.

41:26.191 --> 41:29.190
It's dangerous
and hard to ride,

41:29.191 --> 41:31.647
like an unbroken horse.

41:31.648 --> 41:34.440
[Chuck] That's something
you never really heard me on.

41:34.441 --> 41:38.564
It is not easy,
not easy at all.

41:38.565 --> 41:42.564
But I guess you'll have
a long time to think about it.

41:42.565 --> 41:46.647
They call this getting
what you deserve, don't they?

41:46.648 --> 41:50.190
It's coming for all of us.

41:50.191 --> 41:52.647
[sighs]

41:52.648 --> 41:56.064
What about Jock--

41:56.065 --> 41:58.023
is he left standing?

41:58.024 --> 42:00.232
I just caught up
with the man...

42:03.191 --> 42:05.522
You are a real troublemaker,
Rhoades.

42:05.523 --> 42:06.981
Runs in my blood.

42:06.982 --> 42:08.231
[door closes]
Runs in your kind.

42:08.232 --> 42:09.981
You take that to mean ethnic,
fine.

42:09.982 --> 42:12.981
Or New Yorkers. Or guys with
hair all over their faces.

42:12.982 --> 42:14.856
[laughs]
That's just like you--

42:14.857 --> 42:17.898
focused on a man's beard
with so much intensity

42:17.899 --> 42:20.273
you miss his foot coming up
to kick you in the gonads.

42:20.274 --> 42:21.356
Good luck there, pard.

42:21.357 --> 42:23.064
Ah. Don't need luck.

42:23.065 --> 42:24.398
No.

42:24.399 --> 42:25.981
You know, the last time
we were in here,

42:25.982 --> 42:28.023
in what was my office,

42:28.024 --> 42:30.190
it didn't turn out well
for me.

42:30.191 --> 42:33.190
And I told myself I wouldn't
step foot back in this place

42:33.191 --> 42:35.481
until it was you
who'd be sent packing.

42:35.482 --> 42:37.106
[Chuck] And that is today.

42:37.107 --> 42:39.814
That is right now.

42:39.815 --> 42:42.440
How're those low hangers
feeling?

42:42.441 --> 42:45.148
Heavy, full,
and ready to shoot.

42:45.149 --> 42:47.939
You think just 'cause I had
an overzealous underling,

42:47.940 --> 42:49.898
that I'm gonna take a fall?

42:49.899 --> 42:51.606
I am not.

42:51.607 --> 42:54.564
Connerty acted on his own,
of his own volition.

42:54.565 --> 42:55.939
He screwed up.

42:55.940 --> 42:57.647
So now he's screwed.
Not me.

42:57.648 --> 43:01.106
You came to me on biblical
grounds a short time ago.

43:01.107 --> 43:03.440
And when you left,
it occurred to me

43:03.441 --> 43:07.023
that faith can be
a beautiful thing,

43:07.024 --> 43:10.440
except when
it's misplaced.

43:10.441 --> 43:13.356
♪ dramatic music ♪

43:13.357 --> 43:15.647
[Connerty] I'm not legally
allowed to listen to this--

43:15.648 --> 43:17.856
[Jock] If I order it,
it's fucking legal.

43:17.857 --> 43:20.481
[Jock] Now, you get your hands
on that fucking tape--

43:20.482 --> 43:23.772
♪♪♪

43:23.773 --> 43:26.606
So, the ballsack has to feel
at least a twinge by now.

43:26.607 --> 43:29.814
How the fuck...?

43:29.815 --> 43:31.315
♪♪♪

43:31.316 --> 43:32.898
[Chuck] I had an instinct that

43:32.899 --> 43:34.522
[Chuck] at least some of
what Connerty did

43:34.523 --> 43:36.981
[Chuck] would be
at your direction...

43:36.982 --> 43:39.273
♪ dramatic music ♪

43:39.274 --> 43:41.772
[Connerty] We are running down
some promising leads and--

43:41.773 --> 43:43.814
[cellphone vibrates]

43:43.815 --> 43:46.564
This could be the call.

43:46.565 --> 43:47.814
Connerty...

43:47.815 --> 43:51.939
♪♪♪

43:51.940 --> 43:53.689
[Connerty] No,
I'll be right there.

43:53.690 --> 43:56.814
[Connerty] Good work.

43:56.815 --> 43:59.231
Good luck finishing off
the Rhoadeses.

43:59.232 --> 44:02.856
♪♪♪

44:02.857 --> 44:06.647
♪♪♪

44:06.648 --> 44:10.190
♪♪♪

44:10.191 --> 44:11.647
[groans]

44:11.648 --> 44:13.939
You really did it...

44:13.940 --> 44:16.689
got me
right in the onions...

44:16.690 --> 44:19.190
[shoe slams]

44:19.191 --> 44:20.814
[shoe slams]

44:20.815 --> 44:23.814
[Chuck] So, no, Bryan, no.

44:23.815 --> 44:26.273
[breathes deeply]

44:26.274 --> 44:28.772
When it comes to me, the thing
you've got to learn is:

44:28.773 --> 44:31.690
no one's left standing.

44:43.773 --> 44:48.023
[Rudy] ♪ Ma il mio mistero
è chiuso in me ♪

44:48.024 --> 44:51.148
♪ Il nome mio nessun saprà ♪

44:51.149 --> 44:55.647
♪ No, no, sulla tua bocca ♪

44:55.648 --> 44:58.731
♪ Lo diro ♪

44:58.732 --> 45:02.315
♪ Quando la luce ♪

45:02.316 --> 45:05.982
♪ Splenderà ♪

45:07.982 --> 45:10.772
My dude, that was...
I have like tears in my eyes,

45:10.773 --> 45:12.647
and I don't even own
that Three Tenors album.

45:12.648 --> 45:15.231
My father was a--

45:15.232 --> 45:17.398
look, I'll sing for you
another time.

45:17.399 --> 45:19.981
For now, let's talk
Nigerian Oil Warrants.

45:19.982 --> 45:21.398
You talk. I'll listen.

45:21.399 --> 45:22.981
They are highly
illiquid instruments.

45:22.982 --> 45:24.356
There's no real market
for them.

45:24.357 --> 45:26.064
So the few brokers
who deal in them

45:26.065 --> 45:28.148
can set almost any price.

45:28.149 --> 45:30.106
You invest
a few million dollars,

45:30.107 --> 45:32.273
we wait a week,
and I have them revalued.

45:32.274 --> 45:33.606
How high?

45:33.607 --> 45:35.315
Units that cost you,
say, ten grand each

45:35.316 --> 45:37.064
could suddenly be valued
at a hundred grand.

45:37.065 --> 45:39.274
Or two.
Or five hundred.

45:40.607 --> 45:42.898
For a few million dollars
we can balloon these things up

45:42.899 --> 45:46.564
and basically state that
the firm is even on the year.

45:46.565 --> 45:49.731
♪♪♪

45:49.732 --> 45:50.814
So,
what do you think...?

45:50.815 --> 45:55.440
♪ dramatic music ♪

45:55.441 --> 45:56.772
[cork pops]

45:56.773 --> 45:58.647
[door opens]

45:58.648 --> 46:01.398
[door closes]

46:01.399 --> 46:03.441
Hello there.

46:05.149 --> 46:08.316
You said I was foolish
for wishing for a miracle.

46:10.024 --> 46:13.064
But I guess
they do happen--

46:13.065 --> 46:15.482
when you make them happen.

46:17.107 --> 46:19.316
I'm grateful you got
my suspension lifted.

46:22.149 --> 46:24.689
Well, I'm glad that
it all worked out.

46:24.690 --> 46:26.023
[chuckles]

46:26.024 --> 46:29.772
♪ dramatic music ♪

46:29.773 --> 46:31.356
[sighs]

46:31.357 --> 46:33.564
♪♪♪

46:33.565 --> 46:35.315
[exhales sharply]

46:35.316 --> 46:38.148
♪♪♪

46:38.149 --> 46:40.981
♪♪♪

46:40.982 --> 46:42.856
Grab me a glass.

46:42.857 --> 46:44.190
I'll come join you.

46:44.191 --> 46:47.731
♪♪♪

46:47.732 --> 46:49.564
[shoes scraping]

46:49.565 --> 46:51.522
♪♪♪

46:51.523 --> 46:53.522
[tablet dings, vibrates]

46:53.523 --> 46:57.647
♪♪♪

46:57.648 --> 47:01.689
♪♪♪

47:01.690 --> 47:05.814
♪♪♪

47:05.815 --> 47:08.647
[sighs]

47:08.648 --> 47:12.898
♪♪♪

47:12.899 --> 47:17.398
♪♪♪

47:17.399 --> 47:21.856
♪♪♪

47:21.857 --> 47:26.148
♪♪♪

47:26.149 --> 47:28.856
Did you even
fucking try?

47:28.857 --> 47:31.231
♪♪♪

47:31.232 --> 47:33.564
No. I didn't.

47:33.565 --> 47:35.898
I could explain.

47:35.899 --> 47:37.148
But no.

47:37.149 --> 47:39.399
[Chuck] [sighs]
Yeah. I thought not.

47:41.441 --> 47:42.399
Watch the kids.

47:42.400 --> 47:44.106
Where are you going--

47:44.107 --> 47:45.564
Out.

47:45.565 --> 47:47.564
When are you coming home?
I don't know.

47:47.565 --> 47:49.273
But you are coming home?

47:49.274 --> 47:51.898
I don't know.

47:51.899 --> 47:54.064
[sighs]

47:54.065 --> 47:56.939
♪♪♪

47:56.940 --> 48:00.064
♪♪♪

48:00.065 --> 48:02.772
[door opens and slams]

48:02.773 --> 48:06.273
♪♪♪

48:06.274 --> 48:09.898
♪♪♪

48:09.899 --> 48:12.273
[scoffs]

48:12.274 --> 48:15.481
♪♪♪

48:15.482 --> 48:18.607
♪♪♪

48:24.482 --> 48:26.772
[car door opens]

48:26.773 --> 48:28.315
Hold up.

48:28.316 --> 48:30.607
[car door closes]

48:35.191 --> 48:36.564
You're not under arrest.

48:36.565 --> 48:40.191
But it would be good
if you act like you are...

48:43.441 --> 48:45.356
[exhales heavily]

48:45.357 --> 48:48.481
♪ dramatic music ♪

48:48.482 --> 48:51.856
♪♪♪

48:51.857 --> 48:55.440
♪♪♪

48:55.441 --> 48:57.231
Let's talk
Nigerian Oil Warrants.

48:57.232 --> 48:58.856
You talk. I'll listen.

48:58.857 --> 49:00.315
That right there is

49:00.316 --> 49:03.315
the very picture
of criminal conduct.

49:03.316 --> 49:05.815
And the part where
I refuse and walk out?

49:07.690 --> 49:09.231
Thank you, Rudy.

49:09.232 --> 49:10.856
But you were singing
"Nessun Dorma" before,

49:10.857 --> 49:12.647
which is about
somebody hiding something.

49:12.648 --> 49:14.481
Which makes me wonder why
that particular aria

49:14.482 --> 49:16.772
was in your mouth.
So it's a no for now.

49:16.773 --> 49:19.148
I'll learn to live without
the Nigerian Warrants. And you.

49:19.149 --> 49:22.689
♪♪♪

49:22.690 --> 49:23.898
You're a charming tenor.

49:23.899 --> 49:25.647
Do more of that.
Less of this.

49:25.648 --> 49:28.023
♪♪♪

49:28.024 --> 49:30.606
♪♪♪

49:30.607 --> 49:34.440
It seems there was
a camera malfunction...

49:34.441 --> 49:36.856
I see.

49:36.857 --> 49:38.481
Well, in that case,
I'd like to speak to--

49:38.482 --> 49:42.315
Or at least
that was to be the case

49:42.316 --> 49:44.814
when you balked
at the illicit deal.

49:44.815 --> 49:49.606
But, uh [chuckles]
I've lost my taste

49:49.607 --> 49:51.981
for this particular set-up
right now.

49:51.982 --> 49:53.564
Have you?

49:53.565 --> 49:54.690
Mm.

49:56.274 --> 49:59.606
When I look at the shambles
my life has become--

49:59.607 --> 50:03.481
from my firing,
to my public disgrace,

50:03.482 --> 50:06.148
to my election
with strings attached,

50:06.149 --> 50:09.064
to the destruction
of my marriage,

50:09.065 --> 50:13.939
to my family
falling into disrepair--

50:13.940 --> 50:17.398
ah, did I make mistakes
to cause it?

50:17.399 --> 50:19.939
Perhaps.

50:19.940 --> 50:22.564
♪♪♪

50:22.565 --> 50:24.689
But a truer reckoning is:

50:24.690 --> 50:28.814
it all tracks
back to one source.

50:28.815 --> 50:31.647
One man.

50:31.648 --> 50:36.606
A man so corrosive,
so virulently infective

50:36.607 --> 50:40.064
as to strip me of every
good quality I ever had:

50:40.065 --> 50:44.106
my kindness, my empathy,
my sense of justice.

50:44.107 --> 50:46.564
Maybe even
my ability to love.

50:46.565 --> 50:48.231
[chuckles]

50:48.232 --> 50:52.564
And that very man

50:52.565 --> 50:55.190
charged me with
arresting you

50:55.191 --> 50:59.481
in order to force you
back into his employ.

50:59.482 --> 51:02.898
He wants me to come back
to work for him?

51:02.899 --> 51:04.856
At Axe Capital.
He wants that?

51:04.857 --> 51:06.814
Yes,

51:06.815 --> 51:10.356
which gives us an opening.

51:10.357 --> 51:13.106
[Chuck] I don't want
to force you.

51:13.107 --> 51:16.647
[Chuck] I want you to go back
willingly, but as if I had,

51:16.648 --> 51:20.440
and I want you to help me
take him down,

51:20.441 --> 51:23.939
[Chuck] once and for all.

51:23.940 --> 51:28.148
♪ dramatic music ♪

51:28.149 --> 51:33.064
♪♪♪

51:33.065 --> 51:38.023
♪♪♪

51:38.024 --> 51:39.981
[Taylor] I should have known
what would happen.

51:39.982 --> 51:41.522
I once confessed
to you that

51:41.523 --> 51:43.564
competition brought on
vertigo-like symptoms in me.

51:43.565 --> 51:45.440
Well. I certainly feel faint
right now.

51:45.441 --> 51:47.106
Tighten your stomach.

51:47.107 --> 51:49.148
It'll push the blood
back up into your brain.

51:49.149 --> 51:51.315
You'll feel better.
Won't help my firm.

51:51.316 --> 51:53.606
Or my balance sheet.
Which you destroyed.

51:53.607 --> 51:55.273
I didn't make you
cook the books though.

51:55.274 --> 51:56.939
That was all you.

51:56.940 --> 51:59.689
I figured an extra quarter
or two without redemptions

51:59.690 --> 52:01.481
and disruptions
and I could make a comeback.

52:01.482 --> 52:03.190
Well.
We always think we can.

52:03.191 --> 52:05.481
But then you had your friend
waiting to arrest me.

52:05.482 --> 52:06.939
So I can't.

52:06.940 --> 52:08.607
[chuckles]

52:09.857 --> 52:12.273
He's no friend of mine,
believe me.

52:12.274 --> 52:13.981
[Axe] Just a useful tool.

52:13.982 --> 52:16.064
[Axe] And I wasn't gonna
let him take you to jail.

52:16.065 --> 52:17.356
As long as...

52:17.357 --> 52:19.647
Yes. As long as
I come under heel.

52:19.648 --> 52:21.689
Well.
Don't think of it like that.

52:21.690 --> 52:24.273
Or do.
Whichever.

52:24.274 --> 52:27.856
But, yes,
you are coming back to me.

52:27.857 --> 52:31.606
You were such
a worthy fucking adversary

52:31.607 --> 52:34.148
that even with
a much smaller bankroll

52:34.149 --> 52:37.856
you cost me my relationship
and pushed me to a stalemate.

52:37.857 --> 52:39.231
Right until the very end...

52:39.232 --> 52:41.689
So, yeah,
I want you on my side.

52:41.690 --> 52:43.356
It won't be forever.

52:43.357 --> 52:46.356
I'll walk away soon enough and
your firm will have survived.

52:46.357 --> 52:47.647
Will it have?

52:47.648 --> 52:48.731
That's gonna be up to you.

52:48.732 --> 52:51.356
But it can.
It should.

52:51.357 --> 52:52.856
You're still you.

52:52.857 --> 52:55.273
So how would it work--
I keep my own shingle?

52:55.274 --> 52:58.356
Yes.
Under my banner.

52:58.357 --> 53:00.064
And you and I
are going to, what,

53:00.065 --> 53:01.814
bullshit about ideas
all day long?

53:01.815 --> 53:03.731
We don't have to be
best friends.

53:03.732 --> 53:05.315
Or friends of any kind.

53:05.316 --> 53:07.064
I just want your brain.

53:07.065 --> 53:08.689
[Axe] And it won't all
be bad for you.

53:08.690 --> 53:10.481
We'll pre-set
a bonus structure.

53:10.482 --> 53:12.606
And you will know exactly
where you will end up.

53:12.607 --> 53:14.231
That will be
a signed document.

53:14.232 --> 53:16.731
[Axe] It will. And we will
also have a separate,

53:16.732 --> 53:18.564
special document,
signed by Rhoades too,

53:18.565 --> 53:20.273
that says
at a date certain

53:20.274 --> 53:22.731
whatever he has on you
disappears forever.

53:22.732 --> 53:26.106
♪♪♪

53:26.107 --> 53:29.731
♪♪♪

53:29.732 --> 53:33.106
♪♪♪

53:33.107 --> 53:36.064
Where we at?

53:36.065 --> 53:38.440
I'm going back to work
at Axe Capital.

53:38.441 --> 53:39.899
Will you come with me?

53:42.107 --> 53:43.940
[sighs]

53:46.441 --> 53:48.064
In.

53:48.065 --> 53:51.606
Chuck Rhoades wants to use me
to help him nail Axe.

53:51.607 --> 53:54.190
Crazy.

53:54.191 --> 53:55.981
Are you going to
do it?

53:55.982 --> 53:57.689
I told him I would.

53:57.690 --> 54:00.772
And I made Axe believe I was
done trying to destroy him.

54:00.773 --> 54:02.856
But I learned something:

54:02.857 --> 54:05.023
they're both lined up
to destroy each other.

54:05.024 --> 54:07.440
At the right moment when
both have their guns raised,

54:07.441 --> 54:09.398
I'll step out of the way
and let it happen.

54:09.399 --> 54:10.814
I'll help it happen.

54:10.815 --> 54:12.356
They'll put each other
in the ground

54:12.357 --> 54:14.939
and I'll go about
my fucking business.

54:14.940 --> 54:17.939
♪ dramatic music ♪

54:17.940 --> 54:22.689
♪♪♪

54:22.690 --> 54:27.481
♪♪♪

54:27.482 --> 54:32.273
♪♪♪

54:32.274 --> 54:34.939
[sighs]

54:34.940 --> 54:38.315
♪♪♪

54:38.316 --> 54:41.939
♪♪♪

54:41.940 --> 54:46.064
[door opens, footsteps approach]

54:46.065 --> 54:47.522
Hey.

54:47.523 --> 54:49.190
Hey.

54:49.191 --> 54:51.023
Some day.

54:51.024 --> 54:52.647
[chuckling]
Yeah.

54:52.648 --> 54:55.898
Look, um, that thing
with Rebecca,

54:55.899 --> 54:57.315
I didn't mean
to put you in a--

54:57.316 --> 54:58.940
Nope.
I'm not here for that.

55:00.899 --> 55:02.273
I want to thank you.

55:02.274 --> 55:03.606
I don't know how--

55:03.607 --> 55:05.149
You don't even have to.

55:06.940 --> 55:10.273
And I don't want to
stay at home tonight.

55:10.274 --> 55:11.689
Oh.

55:11.690 --> 55:14.148
Or at some hotel.

55:14.149 --> 55:17.982
Oh...
[stammers]

55:27.482 --> 55:29.647
Oh. Shit.

55:29.648 --> 55:32.772
Six maids
and they leave it like this...

55:32.773 --> 55:34.814
You can't sleep in Dean
and Gordie's room,

55:34.815 --> 55:36.356
'cause they have small beds.

55:36.357 --> 55:39.024
And art is piled all over
the other rooms.

55:43.690 --> 55:45.732
You know what?

55:50.316 --> 55:52.064
We can do this.

55:52.065 --> 55:54.191
[sheet fluttering]

56:09.316 --> 56:11.106
Welp.

56:11.107 --> 56:13.856
♪ dramatic music ♪

56:13.857 --> 56:16.898
Text me what you want
for breakfast in the morning,

56:16.899 --> 56:19.064
I'll let Chef Ryan know.

56:19.065 --> 56:23.356
♪♪♪

56:23.357 --> 56:27.731
♪♪♪

56:27.732 --> 56:31.190
And, you know,
if you want to talk,

56:31.191 --> 56:33.106
I'm right down the hall.

56:33.107 --> 56:37.106
♪♪♪

56:37.107 --> 56:38.939
Have a good night.

56:38.940 --> 56:42.315
♪♪♪

56:42.316 --> 56:45.939
♪♪♪

56:45.940 --> 56:46.981
[door closes]

56:46.982 --> 56:51.564
♪♪♪

56:51.565 --> 56:54.440
[sighs]

56:54.441 --> 56:58.772
♪♪♪

56:58.773 --> 57:00.939
[exhales heavily]

57:00.940 --> 57:03.981
♪ dramatic music ♪

57:03.982 --> 57:07.481
♪♪♪

57:07.482 --> 57:11.273
♪♪♪

57:11.274 --> 57:14.731
♪♪♪

57:14.732 --> 57:16.731
[elevator dings]

57:16.732 --> 57:19.981
[indistinct conversations]

57:19.982 --> 57:24.023
♪♪♪

57:24.024 --> 57:28.106
♪♪♪

57:28.107 --> 57:32.148
♪♪♪

57:32.149 --> 57:36.107
♪♪♪

57:37.940 --> 57:39.647
Hi, Taylor!
Hi, Mafee!

57:39.648 --> 57:41.107
